news.title: Goa: Departments to get 20 days to submit reports on land conversion
news.para: In case these authorities fail to submit their reports to the revenue department within 20 days, the collector concerned will proceed with the land conversion process on the basis of available information.

news.title: YEIDA seeks answers from firms on how to control dust at construction sites
news.para: Officials said they are exploring soil stabilisation methods that can restrict construction dust from flying in the area, a major cause of air pollution especially in the winter season.

news.title: Panel to identify dwellings within forest buffer zones in Goa
news.para: ​Once identified, these structures will be incorporated in the Zonal Master Plan (ZMP) of the respective eco-sensitive zone which is being prepared by the town and country planning (TCP) department.

news.title: Land documents to be linked to owner's email, phone: Goa law minister
news.para: ​The idea, Cabral said, was to link the land ownership documents with the emails IDs and mobile numbers of the owners, so that they receive an automated alert once any attempt is made to tamper with or sell their properties.

news.title: Nashik civic body restarts playing drums in front of tax defaulters' houses
news.para: NMC teams are visiting the houses of the big tax defaulters and playing drums there. So far, the civic body has collected Rs 5.5 crore from the tax defaulters.

news.title: In demand: 443 applicants for e-auction of 34 plots in Noida
news.para: After the end of the e-auction process, officials found that "exorbitant" and "impractical" bids were made for eight plots, which were as high as 16 times their reserve price.

news.title: GRAP curbs no obstacle to Noida airport construction: Officials
news.para: The greenfield airport is coming up in Jewar, some 75 km off Delhi, along the Yamuna Expressway. The airport is being developed in four phases and the first phase is scheduled to be completed by September 2024.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace Developers posts Rs 7.51 crore net loss in Q2 FY23
news.para: Mahindra Lifespaces' net consolidated income stood at Rs 73.82 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of 12.36 per cent from Rs 65.70 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Indigo Paints' net profit jumps 173.8% to $4.47 million in Q2 FY23
news.para: Net profit jumped 173.8% to 370.9 million Indian rupees ($4.47 million) for the three months ended Sept. 30, from 135.5 million rupees a year earlier, the Pune-based company said in an exchange filing.

news.title: Shriram Properties' sales bookings climb 27% to Rs 747 crore in Apr-Sept 2022
news.para: Aggregate sales value stood at Rs 435 crores in second quarter, reflecting a growth of 39 per cent against Rs 313 crores in the first quarter of FY23.

news.title: ED attaches Shine City's properties worth Rs 18 crore in money laundering case
news.para: The ED had lodged a case of Prevention of Money Laundering Act, 2002, against Shine city Infra Project Private Limited for siphoning off crores from investors across the state in January 2021.

news.title: Janhvi Kapoor's family buys Rs 65-crore duplex in Mumbai's Bandra
news.para: The daughter of late actress Sridevi has bought the apartment spread over 8,669 sq ft built up area on the first and second floor of Kubelisque Building on Pali Hill’s Union Park Road.

news.title: ED files charge sheet against SRS group, promoters in money laundering case
news.para: "The accused duped innocent buyers by promising them to deliver flats, plots, commercial spaces etc. however, they failed to deliver the projects. The real estate projects were mortgaged to avail loans from banks and other financial institutions," ED said.

news.title: China Evergrande chairman's Hong Kong mansion seized by bank
news.para: The bank appointed receivers to take over the 5,000 sq ft (465 sq m) mansion on Nov. 1, according to a filing. Saddled with more than $300 billion in total liabilities, the defaulted Chinese property developer has already seen many of its assets, both in mainland China and Hong Kong, seized by creditors.

news.title: UK investors pull $208 million from property funds in October 2022
news.para: UK investors withdrew 184 million pounds ($207.66 million) from property funds in October, the biggest monthly outflows since June 2021, Calastone said.
